INTRODUCTION
In today’s rapidly evolving digital world, digital literacy has become an essential skill for students across all disciplines, including engineering. It not only involves the ability to use digital tools effectively but also includes understanding how to communicate professionally, collaborate online, and stay safe from cyber threats.
This project was designed to provide hands-on experience with various digital platforms and tools that are commonly used in academic and professional environments. It also aimed to build awareness regarding responsible online behavior and cybersecurity practices.
Through this project, I explored tools such as GitHub, LinkedIn, HackerRank, and Google Forms. Additionally, I learned the importance of structured communication through professional emails and gained insights into cybercrime and its prevention. This project has significantly contributed to improving my technical, communication, and digital awareness skills.
TASK 1: DIGITAL LITERACY INFOGRAPHIC
In this task, I created a Digital Literacy Infographic using Canva, an online graphic design platform. The objective of this task was to visually represent key concepts of digital literacy in a simple and engaging manner.
The infographic included several important elements such as the definition of digital literacy, commonly used digital tools for students, safe internet practices, professional online presence, and email etiquette. Tools like Google Docs, GitHub, and LinkedIn were highlighted to show their importance in academic and professional growth.
One of the major challenges in this task was organizing a large amount of information into a single visually appealing layout without compromising clarity. I focused on maintaining a balance between text and visuals to ensure readability and effectiveness.
This task helped me develop skills in visual communication, content organization, and design thinking. It also enhanced my understanding of how information can be presented in a concise yet impactful manner.
TASK 2: DIGITAL PORTFOLIO
The objective of this task was to create and maintain a professional digital portfolio using platforms like GitHub and LinkedIn. These platforms are widely used in the industry to showcase skills, projects, and achievements.
I created and updated my GitHub profile by organizing repositories and uploading project files. GitHub serves as a version control platform and allows developers to manage and share their code efficiently. It is an essential tool for collaboration and project management.
Additionally, I created a LinkedIn profile to establish my professional identity. I added details such as my academic background, field of study, and career interests. LinkedIn helps in building professional connections and staying updated with industry trends.
This task made me realize the importance of having a strong online presence. In the future, I plan to continuously update my profiles with new projects, certifications, and skills, which will be beneficial for internships and job opportunities.
TASK 3: CODING & COLLABORATION PLATFORMS
In this task, I explored various digital platforms used for coding and collaboration. I created an account on HackerRank and solved a beginner-level programming problem. This helped me understand basic coding logic and improve my problem-solving skills.
HackerRank is a widely used platform for practicing coding problems and preparing for technical interviews. Solving problems on such platforms enhances logical thinking and programming ability.
In addition to this, I created a Digital Literacy Quiz using Google Forms. The quiz included multiple-choice and short-answer questions related to digital tools, online safety, and communication. I also linked the form to Google Sheets, which allowed automatic collection and organization of responses.
This task demonstrated how digital tools can be effectively used for learning, assessment, and collaboration. It also improved my ability to use online platforms efficiently for academic purposes.
TASK 4: EMAIL ETIQUETTE & SOCIAL MEDIA AWARENESS
This task focused on developing professional communication skills and understanding responsible social media behavior.
I drafted two professional emails: one requesting an assignment extension from a professor and another expressing interest in a summer internship. While writing these emails, I ensured proper structure, including a clear subject line, formal greeting, well-organized body, and appropriate closing.
I also created a checklist of social media do’s and don’ts. This included guidelines such as maintaining a professional profile, avoiding sharing sensitive information, verifying content before posting, and refraining from offensive or inappropriate behavior.
Reflection:
Poor digital communication can lead to misunderstandings and missed opportunities. For example, an unprofessional or unclear email to a professor may result in a delayed response or negative impression. This can be avoided by using proper email etiquette, maintaining clarity, and being respectful in communication.
This task helped me understand the importance of professionalism in digital communication and how it impacts academic and career growth.
TASK 5: CYBERCRIME AWARENESS
In this task, I studied cybercrime with a focus on phishing attacks. Phishing is a type of cybercrime where attackers impersonate trusted entities to steal sensitive information such as passwords, banking details, or OTPs.
A typical phishing attack involves sending fake emails or messages that create a sense of urgency, prompting users to click on malicious links. These links lead to fake websites that resemble legitimate ones, where users unknowingly enter their personal information.
Students are often targeted because they frequently use digital platforms but may not always be aware of such threats. The consequences of phishing include financial loss, identity theft, and unauthorized access to personal accounts.
Prevention Measures:
To stay safe, users should avoid clicking on suspicious links, verify the authenticity of messages, use strong passwords, enable two-factor authentication, and never share sensitive information like OTPs.
Reflection:
While researching this topic, I was surprised by how realistic phishing attacks can be. It made me realize that even a small mistake can have serious consequences. As a result, I will be more cautious while interacting online and will always verify sources before sharing any personal information.
🏁 CONCLUSION
This Digital Literacy Project has been highly beneficial in enhancing my understanding of digital tools, professional communication, and cybersecurity awareness. It provided practical exposure to platforms that are essential for academic and professional growth.
Through this project, I developed important skills such as problem-solving, digital communication, and online collaboration. I also became more aware of cyber threats and the importance of safe online practices.
Overall, this project has prepared me to effectively use digital technologies in my academic journey and future career, making me a more responsible and informed digital user.

